---
source: tests/conformance/query_v1_matrix.rs
assertion: ee.query.v1 query-file pagination is cursor-based, deterministic, and failure-explicit
schema:
  query_file: ee.query.v1
  pagination: ee.query.pagination.v1
contracts:
  - pagination.limit applies a bounded page size without changing deterministic ordering
  - pagination.cursor resumes from an opaque token scoped to the query shape
  - malformed cursors fail with a stable invalid-cursor error
  - zero or oversized limits fail validation instead of silently falling back
  - pagination composes with pack output while preserving JSON stdout discipline
evidence:
  - tests/conformance/query_v1_matrix.rs::matrix_pagination_limit
  - tests/conformance/query_v1_matrix.rs::matrix_pagination_cursor_first_page
  - tests/conformance/query_v1_matrix.rs::matrix_pagination_invalid_cursor
  - tests/conformance/query_v1_matrix.rs::matrix_pagination_zero_limit
  - src/cli/mod.rs::pagination_from_document
  - src/cli/mod.rs::validate_pagination_object
  - eidetic_engine_cli-4x80
